The FGCU womens soccer team claimed its sixth consecutive Atlantic Sun regular season title Saturday night following a  win over Stetson in DeLand PERIOD 
FGCU has not lost a regular season conference game since October  and finished the season with a  record tying  to Jacksonville earlier this month PERIOD 
On Saturday night the Eagles collected its six additional goals to total  for the season  of them against conference foes PERIOD FGCU forward Tabby Tindell earned a hat trick  her first of the season and third in her career to earn her sixteenth goal this season PERIOD 
Tindells three goals were matched with a goal each from Shea Rhoney Nikki Hudson and Darien Davis PERIOD
After collecting their sixth conference title since  the Eagles will look to earn their fourth postseason title and fourth trip to the NCAA Tournament PERIOD 
With the title FGCU will host the  ASun Conference Championship Tournament beginning with the first round on Oct PERIOD  with the second round and final the following weekend PERIOD FGCU will take on the winner of the first round match between No PERIOD  Kennesaw State and No PERIOD  Stetson on Nov PERIOD  PERIOD
The FGCU mens soccer team will also be tentatively hosting the semifinals of the tournament on Nov PERIOD  PERIOD
